To get all descendant text nodes of an element as a jQuery collection, you can use the `contents()` method and then use the `filter()` method to select only the text nodes. Here's an example:
```
var textNodes = $('#element').contents().filter(function() {
  return this.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE;
});
```
The `contents()` method returns a jQuery collection containing all of the children of the element, including text nodes, comments, and other node types. The `filter()` method filters this collection based on a given condition, in this case selecting only the text nodes by checking the `nodeType` property of each node. The `Node.TEXT_NODE` constant refers to the text node type, which has a value of 3.

Note that this will return a jQuery collection containing all descendant text nodes, not just direct children of the element. If you only want to get the direct children text nodes, you can use the `children()` method instead of `contents()`.
