Here is an example of a Unity URP HLSL shader that can create a pulsing effect over a spatial mapping mesh:
```
Shader "Custom/Pulse" {
    Properties {
        _MainTex ("Albedo (RGB)", 2D) = "white" {}
        _PulseSpeed ("Pulse Speed", Float) = 1.0
    }

    SubShader {
        Tags {"Queue"="Transparent" "RenderType"="Transparent"}
        LOD 200

        CGPROGRAM
        #pragma surface surf Lambert

        sampler2D _MainTex;
        float _PulseSpeed;

        struct Input {
            float2 uv_MainTex;
        };

        void surf (Input IN, inout SurfaceOutput o) {
            fixed4 col = tex2D(_MainTex, IN.uv_MainTex);
            o.Albedo = col.rgb;
            o.Alpha = col.a * (0.5 + 0.5 * sin(_Time.y * _PulseSpeed));
        }
        ENDCG
    }
    FallBack "Diffuse"
}
```
This shader uses the `sin()` function to create a pulsing effect on the object's transparency. The `_PulseSpeed` property can be adjusted in the Unity editor to control the speed of the pulse.

You can apply this shader to the spatial mapping mesh and adjust the properties to get the desired effect.

